<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. If the caller provides buf with only param->value.len bytes (i.e. no extra byte for a NUL), then the non-quoted branch copies param->value.len bytes via memcpy into buf and the subsequent buf[param->value.len] = 0 writes one past the allocated buffer — an out‑of‑bounds access. Because memcpy (from <string.h>) is used without guaranteeing space for the terminator, this can result in a bounds violation (MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17).
</scenario>

